message.content: cs.SD, cs.SD is the sub-category for Sound and Music Computing, which is the most relevant sub-category for this paper as it deals with automatic speech recognition in noisy and reverberant environments. Other likely sub-categories could include cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the paper deals with natural language processing, cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new feature for deep neural networks, cs.SI (Signal Processing) as it deals with processing of audio signals, and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it involves feature extraction from multiple microphone signals.
